<div id="review_1427971572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1427971572" />
    <a title="Barbara Stoker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26072064-barbara-stoker"><img alt="Barbara Stoker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1385594517p2/26072064.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1427971572?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Barbara Stoker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Barbara Stoker" href="/user/show/26072064-barbara-stoker">Barbara Stoker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Readers looking for something new,but epic</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1427971572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1961055528411787367">I received this book as a arc for my honest opinion. <br/>Okay I&apos;ve never been big on any book that has anything to do with the mob, I&apos;ve read some that left me glad it was over. But I read the info on this book thought hey why not, I get to read it for free, if I don&apos;t like it no biggie. So I pick up my tablet and starting reading. Next thing I know my fire alarm is going off because I burnt dinner. I lost all track of time. So I got up shut off stove and sat right back down. I couldn&apos;t stop reading</span>
  <span id="freeText1961055528411787367" style="display:none">I received this book as a arc for my honest opinion. <br />Okay I've never been big on any book that has anything to do with the mob, I've read some that left me glad it was over. But I read the info on this book thought hey why not, I get to read it for free, if I don't like it no biggie. So I pick up my tablet and starting reading. Next thing I know my fire alarm is going off because I burnt dinner. I lost all track of time. So I got up shut off stove and sat right back down. I couldn't stop reading. The characters are written so amazing. I felt as if I was there in Jo's shoes, her pain,fear,confusion,anger,love,passion I felt it all. I was angry on her behalf,wanted to jump in the book hide her and give her a hug. Then we have Greyson and holy cow he was written just as good. I felt his anger at his dad but also his need for his dad's love, his anger,hate,love and joy of his JOBS. His passion, desire, need, concern, confusion and his growing love for Jo. I don't think I have ever been so grateful for signing up for something different in my entire life. I loved every second. So worth the burnt dinner. Because I didn't stop reading until the last page. I honestly didn't care about the world around me just this awesome story. I can honestly say I will be the 1st to read any book for this series or author from here on out. Absolutely a must read. So go to where you buy your books and buy buy buy. Heck buy one as a gift too, your friends will love it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1961055528411787367" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


