<div id="review_1421349179" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1421349179" />
    <a title="Babel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4993628-babel"><img alt="Babel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1325430312p2/4993628.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1421349179?book_show_action=true">Oct 20, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Babel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Babel" href="/user/show/4993628-babel">Babel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4993628-babel?shelf=violence">violence</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4993628-babel?shelf=drama">drama</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4993628-babel?shelf=steamy">steamy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4993628-babel?shelf=bad-boy">bad-boy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1421349179" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6991111054752409031">Irish mob, a girl paying off a family debt, a chemistry than runs as hot as it is dangerous... Good stuff, right?<br/><br/>The story is really catchy. To my mind, the writing style was a little superficial. There wasn&apos;t much of a connection with the characters at first. Though I admit that as the story progressed, they started to feel more real. Joanna has dreams of her own that are squashed by the mob&apos;s ruthless rules, while Greyson is a murderous monster who feels instantly and irrevocably bonded to a w</span>
  <span id="freeText6991111054752409031" style="display:none">Irish mob, a girl paying off a family debt, a chemistry than runs as hot as it is dangerous... Good stuff, right?<br /><br />The story is really catchy. To my mind, the writing style was a little superficial. There wasn't much of a connection with the characters at first. Though I admit that as the story progressed, they started to feel more real. Joanna has dreams of her own that are squashed by the mob's ruthless rules, while Greyson is a murderous monster who feels instantly and irrevocably bonded to a woman he craves. <br /><br />I liked how he's very honest with his feelings for her in his inner dialogue. He frets that she will never feel the same for him. That's a change from so many novels where the man refuses to acknowledge any feelings or attachment to the woman until almost the end of the story.<br /><br />I also enjoyed the conflict that entailed rivalries, mobster violence, betrayal, dirty dealings and dirtier bedtime scenes.<br /><br />Overall, I had fun. The ending was a bit rushed, but I really liked the drama, both emotional and violent, that punctuated this story of mobsters, arranged marriage and hot romance against all odds.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6991111054752409031" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


