    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1435851351" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1435851351" />
    <a title="Renee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15886894-renee"><img alt="Renee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1382417100p2/15886894.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1435851351?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Renee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Renee" href="/user/show/15886894-renee">Renee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1435851351" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2259452708326353129">I received a copy of the book from the author in exchange for an honest review. <br/><br/>I am fast becoming a Kaylee Song fan. This is the third book she&apos;s written that I&apos;ve read and written a review for. She never disappoints me. She always writes strong characters you are invested in. I love that her female characters are always strong ones too. Then there is the heat she always has in her books. It&apos;s actually Kindle melting at times. <br/><br/>Joanna is a O&apos;Brien. Born the niece of a mob boss and a worthless fa</span>
  <span id="freeText2259452708326353129" style="display:none">I received a copy of the book from the author in exchange for an honest review. <br /><br />I am fast becoming a Kaylee Song fan. This is the third book she's written that I've read and written a review for. She never disappoints me. She always writes strong characters you are invested in. I love that her female characters are always strong ones too. Then there is the heat she always has in her books. It's actually Kindle melting at times. <br /><br />Joanna is a O'Brien. Born the niece of a mob boss and a worthless father. She's about to find out just how ruthless her Uncle, who has always taken care of her and her father, can be. Her dad regrettably goes to the rival family the Fitzgerald's and ends up with a gambling debt. A debt that is now the responsibility of Joanna to work off by working for the family as eye candy. This meaning she's seen and not heard and serves drinks at various functions. <br /><br />Grayson is the son of James Fitzgerald, leader of the mob. He's bright, handsome, a total playboy who only does one night stands, and future heir apparent. Chained to a rack and taking a beating for sleeping with the daughter of the second in command he notices Joanna and the attraction is mutual and immediate. He must have her no matter how much he's warned not to. <br /><br />Together Joanna and Grayson begin a scorching love affair and fall hard for each other. They don't tell each other how they feel and they just assume their in it just for the fun of it. After asking Joanna to be his date to a very high profile function they are in a mess. Joanna's Uncle has demands and they are forced into a situation the other thinks they don't want to be in. Can they pull this off? Are they really in this for the right reason or because they are forced? <br /><br />I loved this story from the very first chapter. It was hard to put down as I just had to know what was going to happen next. I loved both Grayson and Joanna each on their own and as a couple. There is a whole host of supporting characters in the book with David, Grayson's half brother, being one I just couldn't stand. He's power hungry and will stop at nothing to become the true heir over Grayson. He is the villain of this love story for sure. <br /><br />If you are a believer in love at first sight, here's your book. I firmly believe in love at first sight but that it takes time to build the true relationship. Kaylee has a fantastic way of pulling you in and not letting you go to the very end. I can not wait to see where she takes Grayson and Joanna next.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2259452708326353129" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


