              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8058883867216931570">Ugh... Here we go again with all these 4-5 star reviews &amp; I just don&apos;t understand it. Did I read the wrong book? I seriously was tempted to DNF this but I kept pushing hoping it would get better. But it was just bad. The editing was terrible, the writing was not great &amp; some of the dialogue was just awful. <br/><br/>***SPOILERS***<br/>For someone that&apos;s suppose to be strong &amp; smart, Joanna was dumb &amp; weak. She comes from a strong, powerful family so you would think that she&apos;d have some sort of backbone. But no</span>
  <span id="freeText8058883867216931570" style="display:none">Ugh... Here we go again with all these 4-5 star reviews &amp; I just don't understand it. Did I read the wrong book? I seriously was tempted to DNF this but I kept pushing hoping it would get better. But it was just bad. The editing was terrible, the writing was not great &amp; some of the dialogue was just awful. <br /><br />***SPOILERS***<br />For someone that's suppose to be strong &amp; smart, Joanna was dumb &amp; weak. She comes from a strong, powerful family so you would think that she'd have some sort of backbone. But no! She's dumb, weak &amp; easy. She gives up the booty to Greyson, who she knows has a horrible rep of being dangerous &amp; a total womanizer, the very first night she's alone with him. She doesn't fight it, just gives it up &amp; without any protection! Can we just stop with these books of females giving it up without using any protection just because the guys is sex?! It's just absolutely ridiculous. <br /><br />They know almost nothing about each other &amp; all the do is bone like rabbits. Then she's forced to marry him for a ridiculous reason &amp; also give up her schooling. She doesn't even really take the time to think about it, just resigns the next day! WHAT?! Absolutely insane! So this wedding starts getting planned &amp; his family are just delusional. His mother is all happy about planning this wedding because she's been wanting to get him settled down for years so she thinks this unpleasant agreement is just great. Ugh! "Catholic women only marry once" The mother actually said this &amp; had me laughing &amp; baffled at the same time. <br /><br />Blah blah blah... All this crap unfolds &amp; shit happens. But when Jo &amp; Greyson reunite they're all "I love you so much!" WHAT? OMG I can't even with this... They were in lust, lust is NOT love!!!<br /><br />I'm so sick of these spineless, complacent women who act like complete bubble heads over hot guys. Then it's insta-lust... cause it's not love!<br /><br />Just stop it!<br /><br /></span>
