              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6908475437635113833">I received this book as an ARC for an honest review. <br/><br/>What would you do if you were forced into a life that you never wanted? What if you knew about this life since birth but thought you would never get dragged into it what would you do? These are the problems Joanna (Jo) is having and now she has to live with what comes next. When Jo&apos;s father racks up a gambling debt that he can&apos;t pay with a rival family Jo agrees to work off her debt. She is there to serve the drinks and look pretty but that is</span>
  <span id="freeText6908475437635113833" style="display:none">I received this book as an ARC for an honest review. <br /><br />What would you do if you were forced into a life that you never wanted? What if you knew about this life since birth but thought you would never get dragged into it what would you do? These are the problems Joanna (Jo) is having and now she has to live with what comes next. When Jo's father racks up a gambling debt that he can't pay with a rival family Jo agrees to work off her debt. She is there to serve the drinks and look pretty but that is all until the day she meets Greyson. There is just something about that man that is like a magnet to her constantly drawing her in. She is warned away from him but everyone knows that it is a lost cause because what Greyson wants Greyson gets.<br /><br />There is something about her that Greyson can't get out of his mind. He figures she will be like all the rest one and done. However once he has her all he wants is more. When he finds out who she is and why she was working in that club that night being around her means something completely different. However one bad call changes everything for both of them in ways they never imagined. <br /><br />This book is amazing it keeps you hooked on this book from the first word to the very end. These characters are battling a lot in this book. From the need for love but the lack of confidence that it is really for them, to the desires that they have for their own lives and what that will mean for others. I think that this book is better than just an escape. I would absolutely recommend this book to anyone and everyone. </span>
