  <span id="freeText13184142928662703704" style="display:none">Omg!! This book is..is I can't even find the words to describe how riveting and terrorizing at the same time. The intensity of each character is remarkably unique. Dam, and I swear to God I thought I was going to break my kindle from squeezing it so tight. If there had been the old Twilight Zone music playing in the background it would of been something cause the intensity keeps building and building!!!<br /><br />He's a monster and she's his prey.<br /><br />Joanna O'Brien, college student and daughter to one of the town's mobsters, is having to work off her father's debt by being eye candy to a rival mobster at a poker game. She never expected to watch someone get whipped and beaten that night, nor did she expect to get captivated and lusting for the man being tortured. After that night she's now deeper than ever tied to him..<br /><br />Grayson Fitzgerald, mobster and the man getting tortured that night. He never expected to lock eyes with her and be frozen in time. He could take the beating his father had ordered for his defiance, he was the son of James Fitzpatrick. Mob Prince to the Irish American Empire after all. He wanted her, No, he was going to have her, he was going to make her scream..his..name. He's a monster, or so they say,<br /><br />Their families will collide, both used as pawns, in a game that will test all their lives.<br /><br />Betrayal, Power, and Lust set's the stage for an exciting story.<br /><br />I was gifted this book by the author for an honest review.</span>
